# Cloudflare Pages security headers for the Jobdun marketing site
# (jobdun.com.au). These are safe for a Flutter/CanvasKit + Google Fonts
# static-asset site. A strict CSP is a deliberate next step — added via
# CSP-Report-Only + a test pass first (it can white-screen CanvasKit if
# set blind), then promoted to enforce.
#
# IMPORTANT: this is the marketing site. Do NOT add X-Robots-Tag:
# noindex, nofollow here — that was the admin console rule, not the
# public marketing surface. Search engines must index jobdun.com.au.
#
# Legal sub-routes (/privacy, /delete-account) are served as static
# HTML from /site/ by Cloudflare Pages and inherit these headers.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=()

# Cache the static Flutter web bundle aggressively. main.dart.js is
# content-hashed by the Flutter build, so this is safe.
/canvaskit/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/icons/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# Don't cache the entry document — the Flutter build swaps it on every
# release and we want the latest index.html.
/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate
